SIMPLE: pusillanimity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pusillanimity
<hw>Pu`sil*la*nim"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pusillanimitas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pusillanimit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
pusillanimous; weakness of spirit; cowardliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The badge of <qex>pusillanimity</qex> and cowardice.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is obvious to distinguished between an act of . . .
<qex>pusillanimity</qex> and an act of great modesty or humility.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cowardliness; cowardice; fear;
timidity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pusillanimous</ent>⟦br⟧
